# My Cloud Portfolio — AWS S3 + CloudFront

A responsive single-page portfolio hosted on AWS S3 and served globally via CloudFront (HTTPS).

## 🌐 Live URL
> https://your-cloudfront-id.cloudfront.net *(replace after deployment)*

---

## 📁 Project Structure
```
my-portfolio/
├── index.html       # Main portfolio page
├── styles.css       # All styles
└── README.md        # This file
```

---

## 🚀 Deployment Steps

### 1. Create S3 Bucket
```bash
# Create bucket (replace YOUR-NAME)
aws s3 mb s3://yourname-portfolio --region us-east-1

# Enable static website hosting
aws s3 website s3://yourname-portfolio \
  --index-document index.html \
  --error-document index.html
```

### 2. Set Bucket Policy (Public Read)
Create a file `policy.json`:
```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::yourname-portfolio/*"
    }
  ]
}
```
Apply it:
```bash
aws s3api put-bucket-policy \
  --bucket yourname-portfolio \
  --policy file://policy.json
```

### 3. Disable Block Public Access
- Go to S3 Console → Your Bucket → Permissions
- Turn OFF "Block all public access"

### 4. Upload Files
```bash
aws s3 sync . s3://yourname-portfolio --exclude "*.md" --acl public-read
```

### 5. Test S3 Endpoint
Visit: `http://yourname-portfolio.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com`

### 6. Create CloudFront Distribution
- Go to **CloudFront Console** → Create Distribution
- Origin Domain: Select your S3 bucket website endpoint
- Viewer Protocol Policy: **Redirect HTTP to HTTPS**
- Default Root Object: `index.html`
- Click **Create Distribution** (takes ~10 minutes to deploy)

### 7. Access via HTTPS
Visit: `https://YOUR_CLOUDFRONT_ID.cloudfront.net`

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- HTML5 / CSS3
- AWS S3 (Static Website Hosting)
- AWS CloudFront (CDN + HTTPS)
- Google Fonts (Space Grotesk, Inter)
- Font Awesome 6 (Icons)
- Git + GitHub (Version Control)

